content:
The Avatar component provides a flexible and accessible way to display user avatars. It's built using Radix UI's primitive components for robust accessibility and theming.

### Exports

*   **`Avatar`**: The root component for displaying an avatar. It accepts standard `AvatarPrimitive.Root` props.
*   **`AvatarImage`**: Component for displaying the avatar image. It accepts `AvatarPrimitive.Image` props.
*   **`AvatarFallback`**: Component for displaying fallback content (e.g., initials) when the image fails to load or is not available. It accepts `AvatarPrimitive.Fallback` props.

### Usage

```tsx
import { Avatar, AvatarImage, AvatarFallback } from '@/components/ui/avatar';

function UserAvatar() {
  return (
    <Avatar>
      <AvatarImage src="https://github.com/shadcn.png" alt="@shadcn" />
      <AvatarFallback>CN</AvatarFallback>
    </Avatar>
  );
}

export default UserAvatar;
```

### Props

*   **`Avatar`**: Can accept any props compatible with `AvatarPrimitive.Root`, including `className` for custom styling.
*   **`AvatarImage`**: Can accept any props compatible with `AvatarPrimitive.Image`, such as `src` and `alt`, as well as `className`.
*   **`AvatarFallback`**: Can accept any props compatible with `AvatarPrimitive.Fallback`, along with `className`.
